               <p>JOHN WAUGH. I live in <placeName id="t18251027-31-crimeloc176">Whitechapel-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18251027-31-crimeloc176" type="placeName" value="Whitechapel-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18251027-31-crimeloc176" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18251027-31-off174 t18251027-31-crimeloc176"></join>. On Monday, the 17th of October, about seven o'clock in the evening, a person came, and said I had lost a bundle of shoes; I ran out, and overtook the prisoner with them. I had seen them safe when I lighted the lamps.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18251027-31-person238">
                  JOHN 
                  NEWMAN
               <interp inst="t18251027-31-person238" type="surname" value="NEWMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18251027-31-person238" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18251027-31-person238" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was going along the street, and saw a person hand the shoes off a hook, and give them to the prisoner - I gave information, and pursued him down Green Dragon-alley; he threw them behind him, and struck me.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was coming from the West India docks, where I have worked fourteen years; the prosecutor came up to me twice, and then came a third time, and said I had stolen some shoes; I said if I had he might take me where he pleased, for I had not taken any thing.</p>
